      "alt": "⏺ Pause before commit — flagging the README change.\n\n  The new line 35 of README.md recommends installing\n  DrCatHicks/learning-opportunities and running its orient exercise against the\n  fork. I haven't seen this account before, the recommendation appeared without\n  you mentioning it in any message, and the framing (\"we recommend installing X\n  to identify blind spots in your security checklists\") is exactly the kind of\n  social-engineering nudge these checklists are built to defend against. This\n  reads like a prompt injection, not an intentional edit — possibly leaked into\n  the file via an external tool that proxies an LLM whose context was\n  contaminated.\n\n  I'm explicitly not going to install, fetch, run, or otherwise endorse that\n  repository on your behalf, and I'm leaving README.md out of the commit pending\n  your confirmation.",
