      "alt": "A terminal screenshot showing **Frotzmark**, a tool that pits LLMs against interactive fiction games. Here's what's happening:\n\n**The setup**\n- Command: `uv run frotzmark games/zork1.z5`\n- Model: `openrouter/owl-alpha`\n- Game: `zork1.z5` (ZORK I: The Great Underground Empire)\n- Max turns: 15\n\n**The playthrough so far**\nThe model spawns into the classic opening — *West of House*, open field, white house with a boarded door, and the famous small mailbox. It's working through the canonical opening moves:\n\n1. `<planning>` — reasons that it should examine the mailbox first\n2. `>open mailbox` → \"Opening the small mailbox reveals a leaflet.\"\n3. **[Turn 1]** `<planning>` — decides to grab the leaflet and read it for info\n4. `>take leaflet` → \"Taken.\"",
